Document: AudioStream
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostream.rst
Summary: Base class for audio stream resources.

Inherits: Resource < RefCounted < Object

AudioStream is the base class for all audio stream resources. It defines the interface that audio playback classes like AudioStreamPlayer and AudioStreamPlayer2D use to play back audio data.

Audio streams are resources that can be loaded and played back. They are typically used for playing music, sound effects, or voice lines. The specific implementation of an AudioStream resource determines how the audio data is stored and decoded. For example, AudioStreamWAV stores uncompressed audio data, while AudioStreamMP3 stores compressed MP3 data.

Key Rule: All audio stream resources must implement the methods defined in the AudioStream class, allowing for a consistent playback interface across different audio formats.
