Document: AudioStream
Path: godot/classes/class_audiostream.rst
Summary: Describes the methods available for the AudioStream class in Godot Engine.

Method: _get_bar_beats() → int
Description: Override this method to return the bar beats of this stream.

Method: _get_beat_count() → int
Description: Overridable method. Should return the total number of beats of this audio stream. Used by the engine to determine the position of every beat. Ideally, the returned value should be based off the stream's sample rate.

Method: _get_bpm() → float
Description: Overridable method. Should return the tempo of this audio stream, in beats per minute (BPM). Used by the engine to determine the position of every beat. Ideally, the returned value should be based off the stream's sample rate.

Method: _get_length() → float
Description: Override this method to customize the returned value of get_length(). Should return the length of this audio stream, in seconds.

Method: _get_parameter_list() → Array[Dictionary]
Description: Return the controllable parameters of this stream. This array contains dictionaries with a property info description format. Additionally, the default value for this parameter must be added to each dictionary in "default_value" field.

Method: _get_stream_name() → String
Description: Override this method to customize the name assigned to this audio stream. Unused by the engine.

Method: _get_tags() → Dictionary
Description: Override this method to customize the tags for this audio stream. Should return a Dictionary of strings with the tag as the key and its content as the value. Commonly used tags include title, artist, album, tracknumber, and date.

Method: _has_loop() → bool
Description: Override this method to return true if this stream has a loop.

Method: _instantiate_playback() → AudioStreamPlayback
Description: Override this method to customize the returned value of instantiate_playback(). Should return a new AudioStreamPlayback created when the stream is played.

Method: _is_monophonic() → bool
Description: Override this method to customize the returned value of is_monophonic(). Should return true if this audio stream only supports one channel.

Method: can_be_sampled() → bool
Experimental: This method may be changed or removed in future versions.
Description: Returns if the current AudioStream can be used as a sample. Only static streams can be sampled.

Method: generate_sample() → AudioSample
Experimental: This method may be changed or removed in future versions.
Description: Generates an AudioSample based on the current stream.

Method: get_length() → float
Description: Returns the length of the audio stream in seconds. If this stream is an AudioStreamRandomizer, returns the length of the last played stream. If this stream has an indefinite length, returns 0.0.

Method: instantiate_playback() → AudioStreamPlayback
Description: Returns a newly created AudioStreamPlayback intended to play this audio stream. Useful for when you want to extend _instantiate_playback() but call instantiate_playback() from an internally held AudioStream subresource.

Method: is_meta_stream() → bool
Description: Returns true if the stream is a collection of other streams, false otherwise.

Method: is_monophonic() → bool
Description: Returns true if this audio stream only supports one channel (monophony), or false if the audio stream supports two or more channels (polyphony).